cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques to generate fine-grained image comparisons. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new model called Neural Naturalist, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves generating comparative language, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
